WEBVTT

00:00.839 --> 00:02.005
<i>Previously on "The Fosters"...</i>

00:02.041 --> 00:03.441
- What's your name?
- A.J.

00:03.475 --> 00:05.176
This is a guy that me
and my brother made up.

00:05.210 --> 00:07.111
We put the symbol in the
windows of our bedrooms.

00:07.146 --> 00:08.313
Like a Bat signal?

00:08.347 --> 00:10.348
- Brandon Foster, piano.
- You're here as a composer.

00:10.382 --> 00:12.350
You're a composer too, huh? I'm Tony.

00:12.384 --> 00:14.085
Man: Brandon, you'll be working with Kat.

00:14.119 --> 00:15.954
There's no way you're pairing me with him.

00:15.988 --> 00:17.055
Sometimes I just want to die.

00:17.089 --> 00:19.057
Maybe we could do some other stuff tonight.

00:19.091 --> 00:21.059
I don't want to do it.
I mean, I want to do it,

00:21.093 --> 00:23.895
but not like this. It's
our first time, and...

00:23.929 --> 00:25.063
We gotta get on the road.

00:25.097 --> 00:26.764
Want a beer?

00:28.934 --> 00:30.702
- A.J.?
- What's wrong?

00:30.736 --> 00:32.070
I let someone sleep here.

00:32.104 --> 00:34.672
Damn it, Callie. Why?

00:34.707 --> 00:36.674
You're fired.

00:37.810 --> 00:39.611
Mariana: Are you almost done in there?

00:39.645 --> 00:40.878
You do know that we're in the worst drought

00:40.913 --> 00:42.547
since 800 A.D., right?

00:42.581 --> 00:43.781
Stef: Oh my gosh, I forgot my conditioner.

00:43.816 --> 00:45.583
Can you go get it from our bathroom, honey?

00:45.618 --> 00:47.685
Okay, well, can you not
waste water while you wait?

00:52.725 --> 00:54.792
Hey, I'm late, and I need to shower too.

00:54.827 --> 00:56.494
Hello?

00:56.528 --> 00:58.730
Why don't you take a spit
bath in the kitchen sink?

00:58.764 --> 01:00.431
Wait, what's a spit bath?

01:00.466 --> 01:01.766
I don't know. Sounds disgusting,

01:01.800 --> 01:04.302
- but I'm next.
- (Aggravated sigh)

01:07.272 --> 01:08.473
Excuse me.

01:08.507 --> 01:10.375
You got wood rot.

01:10.409 --> 01:12.477
Wood rot? That doesn't sound good.

01:12.511 --> 01:14.278
It isn't.

01:14.313 --> 01:17.215
You'll have to open up the
wall. And while you're at it,

01:17.249 --> 01:18.583
I recommend you upgrade to copper plumbing.

01:18.617 --> 01:21.185
- Okay, honey, I need...
- Honey.

01:21.220 --> 01:22.420
- What?
- The guy is here.

01:22.454 --> 01:24.322
Yeah. Hey, how is it going?
I need my conditioner.

01:24.356 --> 01:26.224
- Okay, I will bring it to you.
- I'll get it.

01:26.258 --> 01:28.126
Thank you. It's the blue one in the...

01:28.160 --> 01:30.094
- Okay, I will bring it to you.
- Would you quit pushing me?

01:30.129 --> 01:32.163
- Dear, honey, please.
- Argh!

01:32.197 --> 01:35.199
- So that's your... ?
- Yes.

01:37.403 --> 01:40.071
So, Sophia's coming over today.

01:40.105 --> 01:41.906
How's she doing?

01:41.940 --> 01:43.274
Good, I think.

01:43.308 --> 01:45.877
We're just gonna hang out.

01:45.911 --> 01:47.845
But Robert invited us

01:47.880 --> 01:50.048
to spend Father's Day on his boat.

01:51.183 --> 01:52.884
No, thanks.

01:52.918 --> 01:54.752
You're totally welcome.

01:54.787 --> 01:56.854
Stef: Welcome to what?

01:56.889 --> 01:58.823
If you're gonna spend Father's
Day with him, don't you think

01:58.857 --> 02:00.658
it's weird to keep calling him Robert?

02:00.693 --> 02:02.794
- Morning.
- Morning, love.

02:02.828 --> 02:05.029
- I don't have to go.
- I don't care if you go,

02:05.064 --> 02:06.831
but he's not my dad.

02:06.865 --> 02:09.800
You don't have to always
invite me. It's okay.

02:09.835 --> 02:12.937
Well, listen, Jude, we're
having Mike over on Sunday...

02:12.971 --> 02:14.939
kind of a family
tradition for Father's Day,

02:14.973 --> 02:16.908
you know, to celebrate

02:16.942 --> 02:18.776
the important men in our lives.

02:18.811 --> 02:21.846
I guess we won't have to make
cheese blintzes this year, will we?

02:21.880 --> 02:25.450
- Cheese blintzes?
- Yeah, they were my father's favorites.

02:25.484 --> 02:28.419
My first Father's Day without a father.

02:28.454 --> 02:30.621
It's certainly not gonna be a party

02:30.656 --> 02:32.590
without Frank around to offend somebody.

02:32.624 --> 02:36.394
- I'm sure you'll manage that.
- (Chuckles) That's funny.

02:36.428 --> 02:38.396
Can I invite my dad?

02:38.430 --> 02:39.697
Donald?

02:39.732 --> 02:41.632
- Yeah.
- Why?

02:41.667 --> 02:43.501
You're spending the day with your dad.

02:43.535 --> 02:46.437
- It's a little different.
- How is it different?

02:46.472 --> 02:50.241
Well, for starters, Robert
actually wants to be in my life.

02:50.275 --> 02:52.210
Donald just signed the
papers and walked away.

02:52.244 --> 02:53.377
Robert signed the papers, too.

02:53.412 --> 02:55.213
Is he better because he's rich?

02:55.247 --> 02:57.048
Donald doesn't want
anything to do with you.

02:57.082 --> 02:58.416
- You don't know what he wants.
- It's pretty obvious.

02:58.450 --> 03:00.952
- Why do you hate him so much?
- 'Cause he killed our mother.

03:00.986 --> 03:02.253
- Callie.
- It was an accident.

03:02.287 --> 03:05.123
- Drunk driving is not an accident.
- Okay, that's enough.

03:05.157 --> 03:07.258
If Jude wants to invite Donald...

03:07.292 --> 03:09.861
Then he's welcome to.

03:11.296 --> 03:13.264
Fine.

03:13.298 --> 03:16.167
But don't be surprised
when he doesn't show up.

03:20.906 --> 03:23.107
<i>(Theme song playing)</i>

03:24.943 --> 03:28.012
<i>♪ It's not where you come from ♪</i>

03:28.046 --> 03:31.048
<i>♪ it's where you belong ♪</i>

03:31.083 --> 03:33.885
<i>♪ nothing I would trade ♪</i>

03:33.919 --> 03:35.887
<i>♪ I wouldn't have it ♪</i>

03:35.921 --> 03:37.889
<i>♪ any other way ♪</i>

03:37.923 --> 03:40.892
<i>♪ you're surrounded by love ♪</i>

03:40.926 --> 03:42.894
<i>♪ and you're wanted ♪</i>

03:42.928 --> 03:46.164
<i>♪ so never feel alone ♪</i>

03:46.198 --> 03:48.933
<i>♪ you will always be ♪</i>

03:48.967 --> 03:52.036
<i>♪ right where you belong. ♪</i>

03:54.037 --> 03:59.537
