04:21.233 --> 04:23.067
It's perfect...

04:23.101 --> 04:25.203
- Thank you.
- ... Technically,

04:25.237 --> 04:27.839
but your melody's anemic,

04:27.873 --> 04:29.774
your rhythmic statements are mundane,

04:29.808 --> 04:31.909
and your intervals are reductive.

04:31.944 --> 04:34.912
The whole piece is utterly jejune.

04:34.947 --> 04:37.215
(Stammers)

04:37.249 --> 04:40.785
Considering the amount of time that I had,

04:40.819 --> 04:42.220
I did the best I could.

04:42.254 --> 04:45.957
Those are the five most pathetic
words in the English language.

04:45.991 --> 04:48.960
People who are satisfied with the
best they can do will never be great.

04:48.994 --> 04:50.161
Six, actually.

04:50.195 --> 04:51.829
I'm sorry, what?

04:51.864 --> 04:53.831
Six words.

04:53.866 --> 04:55.900
I never said I was satisfied.

04:55.934 --> 04:57.802
- I just...
- Then start over.

04:59.872 --> 05:01.005
Fine.

05:01.099 --> 05:03.167
Okay, I'll meet you here
at 8:00 tomorrow morning.

05:03.201 --> 05:04.936
Wait, tomorrow?

05:04.970 --> 05:06.938
I gotta sleep at some point.

05:06.972 --> 05:08.973
You have your whole life to sleep.

05:09.007 --> 05:11.208
We have one shot at Disney Hall.

05:11.323 --> 05:13.224
Get inspired.

05:15.260 --> 05:17.061
And take a shower.

05:19.097 --> 05:21.966
We got one working bathroom at home,

05:22.000 --> 05:24.301
six people.

05:24.336 --> 05:27.071
I'm just saying.

05:27.105 --> 05:28.973
How is it going with Kat?

05:29.007 --> 05:31.375
Oh, you know, she's...

05:31.410 --> 05:34.111
A bitch?

05:34.146 --> 05:36.013
Hey, man, we're all bitches.

05:36.048 --> 05:37.982
And this bitch would give his left nut

05:38.016 --> 05:39.950
to compose for Kat.

05:39.985 --> 05:43.020
Well, if it was up to
me, you could have her.

05:43.055 --> 05:45.022
'Cause I'm pretty sure nothing I do

05:45.057 --> 05:46.323
is gonna be good enough for her.

05:46.358 --> 05:48.059
It won't be.

05:48.093 --> 05:50.061
But if you can take the heat,

05:50.095 --> 05:51.996
she's your golden ticket, man.

05:54.132 --> 05:56.967
How do you stay so calm and cool?

05:57.002 --> 05:58.069
I'm a cool dude.

06:01.173 --> 06:03.140
- How's your fugue?
- It's pretty tight.

06:03.175 --> 06:05.142
Can I hear it?

06:05.177 --> 06:07.144
Yeah, sure.

06:22.327 --> 06:25.029
It's so cute.

06:25.063 --> 06:27.064
I ordered it online last week.

06:27.099 --> 06:30.067
Why don't you give it to Isabella yourself?

06:30.102 --> 06:32.169
Um, I think

06:32.204 --> 06:34.205
Ana needs some space.

06:34.239 --> 06:36.340
Well, I'll see that she gets it.

06:36.408 --> 06:38.342
But...

06:38.376 --> 06:41.178
I hope you're still
coming for Father's Day.

06:41.213 --> 06:43.147
It would mean the world to Victor.

06:43.181 --> 06:46.050
And your uncles and cousins will be here,

06:46.084 --> 06:49.186
and everybody is so excited to meet you.

06:49.221 --> 06:51.255
Look.

06:54.426 --> 06:56.260
- Is Ana coming?
- Of course.

06:56.294 --> 06:58.195
She says her brothers
are upset that she's back

06:58.230 --> 06:59.964
and living with you.

06:59.998 --> 07:02.099
They're wary about their sister.

07:02.134 --> 07:06.036
She put us all through a lot.

07:06.071 --> 07:08.072
It's gonna take time to trust her.

07:08.106 --> 07:09.940
But we're family.

07:09.975 --> 07:11.308
And don't worry,

07:11.343 --> 07:13.844
we're gonna keep the
party small and intimate.

07:13.949 --> 07:15.382
Please say you'll come.

07:18.920 --> 07:20.854
Do your moms know you got fired?

07:20.889 --> 07:22.823
I haven't told them yet.

07:22.857 --> 07:25.059
I want to try to find

07:25.093 --> 07:27.962
some other independent
study first, you know,

07:27.996 --> 07:30.064
so they don't totally freak out.

07:32.100 --> 07:33.867
So where's this A.J. guy now?

07:33.902 --> 07:35.736
I don't know.

07:35.770 --> 07:37.738
Living on the streets probably.

07:37.772 --> 07:39.006
Was he cute?

07:39.040 --> 07:42.009
That's not why I tried to help him.

07:42.043 --> 07:43.911
Okay, but he was hot, right?

07:43.945 --> 07:46.046
- Stop it.
- I'm just saying.

07:47.082 --> 07:49.683
How's everything with you?

07:49.718 --> 07:50.784
Fine.

07:50.819 --> 07:51.919
You sure?

07:51.953 --> 07:53.854
Yes.

07:53.888 --> 07:56.624
And I wish that everyone would
stop asking me that question

07:56.658 --> 07:58.592
every five seconds.

07:59.728 --> 08:03.497
- (Cell phone rings)
- Sorry.

08:06.635 --> 08:07.768
Hello.

08:07.802 --> 08:10.671
<i>Hey, it's me... A.J.</i>

08:13.575 --> 08:15.676
- I'll just be right back.
- Okay.

08:20.649 --> 08:23.584
- Are you in juvie? <i>
- I got arrested.</i>

08:23.618 --> 08:25.519
- For huffing.<i>
- Tagging.</i>

08:25.553 --> 08:27.421
<i>Gang signs. But I didn't...</i>

08:27.455 --> 08:29.390
I really don't care.

08:29.424 --> 08:31.759
<i>Callie, please, I need your help.</i>

08:31.793 --> 08:34.761
I tried to help you
and you screwed me over.

08:34.796 --> 08:37.298
<i>I'm not in a gang.</i>

08:37.332 --> 08:38.666
Good for you. I gotta go.

08:38.700 --> 08:40.400
<i>Wait.</i>

08:40.434 --> 08:42.236
<i>There's a skate park on Oceanside.</i>

08:42.270 --> 08:44.203
<i>Go check it out. You'll see.</i>

08:44.239 --> 08:46.440
<i>Please.</i>

08:46.474 --> 08:49.476
<i>Callie. Please?</i>

08:51.379 --> 08:53.347
Do me a favor, lose my number.

08:55.183 --> 08:57.184
Callie.

08:57.218 --> 08:59.086
I spoke with Donald,

08:59.120 --> 09:01.155
and he would like to come tomorrow.

09:01.189 --> 09:03.123
- Okay.
- Is it?

09:03.158 --> 09:05.259
Oh, I won't be here, so
I won't have to see him.

09:05.293 --> 09:08.062
You want to talk about it?

09:08.096 --> 09:09.997
No, thank you.

09:10.031 --> 09:11.865
Sophia's outside.

09:25.180 --> 09:27.114
Look, I'm really sorry about before.

09:27.148 --> 09:29.717
I... I'm on these new meds,

09:29.751 --> 09:31.685
and they make me sort of irritable,

09:31.720 --> 09:33.954
as my mother would say.

09:33.988 --> 09:35.956
It's fine.

09:40.595 --> 09:43.630
You want to get out of here?

09:43.665 --> 09:45.599
Yeah.

09:45.633 --> 09:47.568
Where do you want to go?

09:48.703 --> 09:50.604
Man: Nice one.

09:50.638 --> 09:52.606
What are we looking for?

09:52.640 --> 09:54.608
I'm not exactly sure.

09:58.446 --> 09:59.680
There.

10:02.617 --> 10:04.718
What is it?

10:04.753 --> 10:07.521
It's a Bat signal.

10:16.912 --> 10:21.482
- (Distant band playing)
- (People chattering)

10:29.625 --> 10:31.359
Hey.

10:32.728 --> 10:34.395
We're having a party.

10:34.430 --> 10:35.763
No kidding.

10:35.798 --> 10:38.332
Come on, take a break.

10:38.367 --> 10:41.269
- Come have a beer.
- No, I... I can't.

10:41.303 --> 10:42.370
Just one beer.

10:42.404 --> 10:44.338
No, I... I... I really can't.

10:44.373 --> 10:46.207
How's it going?

10:46.241 --> 10:47.442
It's not.

10:47.476 --> 10:49.377
Yeah, that's right. You know why?

10:49.411 --> 10:51.212
'Cause you're all in your head.

10:51.246 --> 10:52.580
Come on, man, you gotta chillax.

10:52.614 --> 10:54.582
Look, even if I wanted to chillax,

10:54.616 --> 10:56.384
I would still have to
drive home and then get up

10:56.418 --> 10:59.020
at the crack of ass to
get back here by 8:00.

10:59.054 --> 11:00.988
You don't have to get
up at the crack of ass,

11:01.023 --> 11:02.457
'cause your ass can crash in my crib...

11:04.159 --> 11:06.160
On one condition.

11:12.134 --> 11:14.168
One beer and then I gotta get back to work.

11:14.203 --> 11:16.137
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

11:21.009 --> 11:23.845
- What?
- Kat.

11:23.879 --> 11:24.979
Uh-oh.

11:25.013 --> 11:26.948
Brandon.

11:26.982 --> 11:28.216
Get over here.

11:29.251 --> 11:30.952
Go.

11:34.923 --> 11:37.225
Hey. I was just having one beer.

11:37.259 --> 11:38.993
Well, that's no fun.

11:39.027 --> 11:41.195
Come on, let's do Tequila shots.

11:47.035 --> 11:50.004
Hey, A.J. I'm Stef.

11:50.038 --> 11:51.639
What's this?

11:51.673 --> 11:53.641
This is my foster mom.

11:53.675 --> 11:56.010
You asked me for help.

11:56.044 --> 11:58.012
Go ahead, have a seat.

11:58.046 --> 11:59.947
I won't bite.

12:03.886 --> 12:06.521
Callie tells me that you're
looking for your brother,

12:06.555 --> 12:08.689
you think he might be
missing. Does he have a name?

12:08.724 --> 12:11.659
- Is he in trouble?
- Well, you tell me.

12:11.693 --> 12:13.628
I mean, because I ran
away to meet up with him?

12:13.662 --> 12:16.664
- Yeah, but you didn't meet up with him, did you?
- No, he never showed.

12:16.698 --> 12:18.533
Okay, what was the plan if he had showed?

12:18.567 --> 12:20.535
We were gonna go to Arizona.

12:20.569 --> 12:22.804
He said knew some guy that
could get him a job there

12:22.838 --> 12:24.672
in construction.

12:26.698 --> 12:29.433
We just wanted to be together.

12:29.467 --> 12:31.635
You were arrested for tagging, yes?

12:31.669 --> 12:34.671
Yeah, but cops just assume that
'cause I'm black I'm in a gang.

12:34.706 --> 12:36.607
Yeah, well, I don't assume that.

12:36.641 --> 12:38.742
But, you know, it is
illegal to deface property,

12:38.776 --> 12:41.378
even if you are just leaving
a message for someone.

12:41.412 --> 12:42.846
Look, I was gonna turn myself in.

12:42.881 --> 12:45.549
But I knew that once I got back in
the system, I'd be harder to find.

12:45.583 --> 12:47.618
I just wanted Ty to know where I was.

12:47.652 --> 12:49.653
- Ty?
- Tyrone Hensdale.

12:49.687 --> 12:52.322
That's my brother.

12:52.357 --> 12:55.192
Is there any chance that he might
have gone to Arizona by himself?

12:55.226 --> 12:57.494
No, there's no chance.

12:59.597 --> 13:02.499
If he didn't show, it's 'cause
something happened to him.

13:02.533 --> 13:05.168
Okay, fair enough.

13:05.203 --> 13:07.137
I'll see what I can do.

13:09.107 --> 13:11.108
Are you gonna be okay in here?

13:11.142 --> 13:13.343
I'll be fine.

13:13.378 --> 13:15.412
Thank you.

13:32.931 --> 13:34.264
(Applause)

13:34.299 --> 13:36.266
That was fun.

13:36.301 --> 13:38.168
You are fun.

13:38.202 --> 13:40.871
Well, you are fun.

13:40.905 --> 13:42.139
What, does that surprise you?

13:42.173 --> 13:45.008
A little, yeah.

13:45.043 --> 13:47.844
Listen, we got off on the wrong foot.

13:49.180 --> 13:51.915
Do you know what the soul of genius is?

13:51.950 --> 13:53.750
Uh...

13:53.785 --> 13:56.687
Love. That's what Mozart said.

13:56.721 --> 13:59.623
- Love.
- Right.

13:59.657 --> 14:01.792
I need to love you.

14:04.629 --> 14:05.762
Okay.

14:05.797 --> 14:07.698
I also need to pee.

14:07.732 --> 14:09.833
Go for it.

14:12.637 --> 14:13.870
Hey, you.

14:14.906 --> 14:17.541
We are going to Disney Hall.

14:17.575 --> 14:19.810
All right.

14:19.844 --> 14:21.678
And I'm sleeping in tomorrow.

14:21.713 --> 14:22.746
Great.

14:26.751 --> 14:28.719
You're fun.

14:28.753 --> 14:30.554
You're really fun.

14:47.739 --> 14:49.706
(Phone buzzes)

15:15.199 --> 15:17.267
Kat: These kids are so lax.
I haven't heard a single fugue

15:17.301 --> 15:19.169
that's worthy of being
played at Disney Hall.

15:19.203 --> 15:21.304
Okay, see? This is exactly
what I'm talking about.

15:21.339 --> 15:23.407
I'm willing to get up on a
Sunday morning to work with him,

15:23.441 --> 15:25.308
- and he's 30 minutes late.
- What happened, Brandon?

15:25.343 --> 15:27.277
I overslept. I'm sorry.

15:27.311 --> 15:29.079
Did you rewrite your fugue?

15:30.214 --> 15:32.349
No, I didn't get a chance to finish it.

15:32.383 --> 15:34.985
Why? What were you doing all night?

15:36.387 --> 15:38.989
He's obviously not taking
the program seriously.

15:39.023 --> 15:41.058
Tony said he's willing to
compose for two pianists.

15:41.092 --> 15:43.927
Okay, you know what? I did write
a fugue. She didn't like it.

15:43.961 --> 15:45.162
- It was so...
- Jejune.

15:45.196 --> 15:47.330
Yeah, I know. Whatever the hell that means.

15:47.365 --> 15:49.299
And now he's defensive.

15:49.333 --> 15:52.869
I deserve a partner as
talented and dedicated as I am.

15:52.904 --> 15:54.838
Okay, Kat. I hear you.

15:54.872 --> 15:56.973
Let me think about it.

15:57.008 --> 16:00.143
In the meantime, Brandon,
let's hear what you've got.

16:13.851 --> 16:16.700
Robert: "Good for a batch of fresh cookies"

16:16.706 --> 16:18.674
- (Sophia giggles) Yeah.
- Sounds delicious.

16:18.708 --> 16:20.709
- "Good for a day at the movies."
- Always.

16:20.743 --> 16:24.346
- "Good for one car wash." I like that. I like that.
- Yeah.

16:24.380 --> 16:25.714
Oh, I like this one.

16:25.748 --> 16:27.717
"Good for one 20 minute foot rub."

16:27.791 --> 16:29.358
- Can I redeem this right now?
- Oh, yeah.

16:29.392 --> 16:32.161
