18:10.460 --> 18:12.461
and they said that he's a good student,

18:12.495 --> 18:16.265
always followed the
rules until he ran away.

18:16.299 --> 18:18.267
And they won't take him back?

18:18.301 --> 18:20.169
Not everybody gives second chances.

18:20.203 --> 18:23.405
- Or thirds, or fourths.
- Ha-ha. I don't know,

18:23.440 --> 18:25.456
there's just something
about him. He's a good kid.

18:26.157 --> 18:28.257
And I think the longer
he stays in detention,

18:28.283 --> 18:30.962
the more at risk he is of
getting into some real trouble.

18:31.036 --> 18:32.336
You're thinking about fostering him?

18:32.371 --> 18:34.372
No, no, no, no, no. We can't.

18:34.374 --> 18:38.409
But I was thinking about you fostering him.

18:38.443 --> 18:40.978
Me?

18:41.013 --> 18:43.281
Yeah, why not you?

18:55.861 --> 18:58.129
Mariana.

18:58.163 --> 19:00.197
Are you leaving already?

19:00.232 --> 19:02.967
Oh.

19:03.203 --> 19:04.238
I actually haven't gone in yet.

19:07.072 --> 19:08.773
Where's Isabella?

19:08.872 --> 19:11.073
She's with my mother.

19:11.075 --> 19:13.075
Have you gone in?

19:15.746 --> 19:18.748
No. Not yet.

19:18.782 --> 19:20.916
Are you going to?

19:22.052 --> 19:23.753
I don't think so.

19:23.787 --> 19:25.721
Why not?

19:25.756 --> 19:28.624
Because I'm embarrassed.

19:28.659 --> 19:30.660
Of what?

19:30.694 --> 19:33.696
Of being your daughter.

19:35.270 --> 19:36.654
(Knocks on door)

19:40.671 --> 19:42.605
- Hi.
- Hey.

19:42.639 --> 19:43.939
How are you?

19:44.054 --> 19:46.789
Good. Come in.

19:46.823 --> 19:48.858
Thanks.

19:53.730 --> 19:55.531
Happy Father's Day.

19:55.565 --> 19:56.832
Oh, thanks.

19:56.867 --> 19:58.801
These are for your moms.

19:58.835 --> 20:00.803
They love flowers.

20:00.837 --> 20:02.538
That's good.

20:02.572 --> 20:04.640
You... you're, like, a foot taller, huh?

20:04.674 --> 20:07.510
Yeah, my moms say I'm gonna have to
start cutting my pants into shorts.

20:07.544 --> 20:08.844
Yeah, I had that problem
when I was a kid too.

20:08.879 --> 20:10.713
- How tall are you?
- Six feet.

20:10.747 --> 20:12.481
You're gonna be taller. My dad...

20:12.516 --> 20:14.416
your granddad... was six-three.

20:14.451 --> 20:17.753
So is Callie here?

20:17.755 --> 20:19.789
No, she's with her dad...

20:19.823 --> 20:22.358
I mean, Robert.

20:23.660 --> 20:25.394
Yeah.

20:25.428 --> 20:28.464
A friend of mine's
coming over, with his dad.

20:28.498 --> 20:29.299
Okay.

20:29.683 --> 20:31.784
But don't worry, they
don't know that you were,

20:32.119 --> 20:34.187
you know, in prison.

20:35.569 --> 20:37.536
So you don't have to...

20:37.571 --> 20:40.473
Yeah. No, it's...

20:40.507 --> 20:42.308
it's okay, Jude.

20:46.910 --> 20:48.216
Hey, hey.

20:48.519 --> 20:53.256
So Jude doesn't want his dad to know...

20:54.292 --> 20:56.226
about him and me.

20:56.260 --> 20:59.095
I got no problem with that.

20:59.130 --> 21:01.264
The fewer people that know, the better.

21:06.437 --> 21:08.371
Look at all those fake smiles.

21:10.241 --> 21:13.109
- They think I don't know.
- Know what?

21:13.144 --> 21:15.145
That they're sending
me back to the hospital

21:16.679 --> 21:19.064
or to one of those therapy boarding schools

21:19.065 --> 21:20.365
where they lock you up.

21:20.484 --> 21:22.118
- How do you know?
- It's my mom.

21:22.153 --> 21:24.254
She is afraid to leave me alone,

21:24.288 --> 21:25.989
afraid I'll try to hurt myself.

21:26.023 --> 21:27.824
She just wants to get rid of me.

21:27.859 --> 21:29.092
What have they said to you?

21:29.126 --> 21:31.795
Nothing. They're probably just afraid

21:31.829 --> 21:34.231
that I'll run away or...

21:34.265 --> 21:36.233
I don't know.

21:36.267 --> 21:38.835
Are you sure you're not just...

21:38.870 --> 21:41.805
What? Being paranoid?

21:41.839 --> 21:43.740
Because I'm crazy?

21:43.774 --> 21:44.975
You're not crazy.

21:45.009 --> 21:46.877
They're always whispering, okay?

21:46.911 --> 21:50.080
And when I walk into the
room, they shut right up.

21:50.114 --> 21:52.649
There was a girl that
I met in the hospital.

21:52.683 --> 21:55.819
Her parents sent her to one
of those schools in Montana,

21:55.853 --> 21:57.988
and she said it was like a prison.

21:58.022 --> 22:00.023
Can you please talk to my mom?

22:00.057 --> 22:01.992
Talk to me about what?

22:07.832 --> 22:09.866
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings.

22:09.901 --> 22:12.636
Oh, it's okay. I understand.

22:12.670 --> 22:14.738
I'm embarrassed too.

22:14.772 --> 22:17.641
I caused my family a lot of heartache.

22:17.675 --> 22:20.510
Want to know a secret?

22:20.544 --> 22:22.646
I've been walking around
the block for an hour,

22:22.680 --> 22:24.648
trying to get the courage up

22:24.682 --> 22:26.616
to show my face in there.

22:26.651 --> 22:29.819
I'm not even sure my
brothers will speak to me.

22:29.854 --> 22:31.788
But, Mariana,

22:31.822 --> 22:34.357
I'm the only one who needs to feel ashamed.

22:34.392 --> 22:36.493
I'm the one who did all
the bad things, not you.

22:36.527 --> 22:39.329
You and Jesus are pure and innocent,

22:39.363 --> 22:41.431
and no one in there is judging you.

22:43.534 --> 22:45.302
I'm not innocent.

22:45.336 --> 22:46.736
Of course you are. You did nothing wrong.

22:46.771 --> 22:48.438
Yes, I did.

22:48.472 --> 22:49.539
Mariana.

22:49.573 --> 22:53.610
I had sex for the first time,

22:53.644 --> 22:56.146
and not with Mat.

22:57.281 --> 23:00.450
So, anybody following the playoffs?

23:00.484 --> 23:04.187
Mm, Miami's my team, but since LeBron left,

23:04.221 --> 23:06.222
it's been a miserable season.

23:06.257 --> 23:09.092
Yeah. How about you, Donald?
Who do you like in the finals?

23:09.126 --> 23:10.327
Truth is, I'm not much of a sports fan.

23:10.361 --> 23:12.195
Me neither.

23:12.229 --> 23:14.431
So, Donald, what you do for a living?

23:14.465 --> 23:17.367
- I'm a mechanic.
- Oh, nice. You been doing that a long time?

23:17.401 --> 23:20.403
No, I was in commercial
real estate before that.

23:20.438 --> 23:23.206
So am I. We probably know
some of the same people.

23:23.240 --> 23:25.241
I doubt it.

23:25.276 --> 23:27.210
It was a while ago. It was...

23:27.244 --> 23:29.279
it was up in the Bay area.

23:29.313 --> 23:31.381
Adam: So why did you get out?

23:31.415 --> 23:33.283
The grind, you know.

23:33.317 --> 23:35.352
I'm just happier fixing cars.

23:35.431 --> 23:38.967
I hear you. Tough business, huh?

23:39.001 --> 23:42.070
It's not as tough as being
a cop though. Right, Mike?

23:42.104 --> 23:43.972
I don't know any different.

23:44.006 --> 23:47.008
You know, Stef's a cop too.

23:47.043 --> 23:49.110
Oh, yeah, yeah. No, of course.

23:49.145 --> 23:51.112
Well, I think pretty much any profession

23:51.147 --> 23:52.914
has its challenges, right?

23:53.983 --> 23:56.751
So where in the Bay area, Donald?

23:56.786 --> 23:58.720
I know a couple of guys up there.

23:58.754 --> 24:00.021
- Hey.
- Hey.

24:00.056 --> 24:02.057
Sorry, I'm really late.

24:04.093 --> 24:05.960
You look like hell.

24:05.995 --> 24:09.064
Thanks. Happy Father's Day.

24:11.934 --> 24:13.835
Okay, well, who did you have sex with?

24:13.869 --> 24:15.904
- Wyatt.
- And Wyatt is?

24:17.640 --> 24:19.574
(Crying) Callie's ex-boyfriend.

24:21.577 --> 24:24.879
I'm a terrible person,
and I feel like a slut.

24:24.914 --> 24:26.915
Don't you ever say that about yourself.

24:26.949 --> 24:28.917
I cheated on my boyfriend,

24:28.951 --> 24:31.920
and I lost my virginity to
a random boy I barely know.

24:31.954 --> 24:34.489
I'm pretty sure that makes me a slut.

24:34.523 --> 24:36.858
What if I get pregnant
at 15, just like you did?

24:36.892 --> 24:38.793
Did you use protection?

24:38.828 --> 24:40.528
A condom.

24:40.563 --> 24:43.465
But what if it had, like,
a hole in it or something?

24:43.499 --> 24:45.633
- I heard that happens.
- It's pretty unlikely.

24:45.668 --> 24:49.437
I just kind of want to
forget that it ever happened.

24:49.472 --> 24:52.373
Well, why do you think it did happen?

24:53.742 --> 24:56.411
Because Mat didn't want
to have sex with me,

24:56.445 --> 24:59.280
so he could hook up with girls on tour.

24:59.315 --> 25:01.549
Or he didn't want to just have sex with you

25:01.584 --> 25:03.585
your first time, and then leave.

25:03.675 --> 25:06.443
What teenage boy turns down sex?

25:06.478 --> 25:09.580
The good ones. The ones who care about you.

25:09.614 --> 25:11.348
The ones who don't want you to feel

25:11.383 --> 25:13.350
the way you're feeling right now.

25:15.320 --> 25:17.288
Do you think I should tell Callie?

25:21.626 --> 25:24.295
I don't know.

25:24.329 --> 25:27.398
But...

25:27.432 --> 25:29.466
You should probably tell your moms.

25:33.271 --> 25:37.374
I'll tell you one way I think
we're probably a lot alike.

25:37.409 --> 25:39.376
We probably judge ourselves

25:39.411 --> 25:41.979
way harsher than anyone judges us.

25:45.283 --> 25:47.885
So what do you say

25:47.919 --> 25:49.920
we go to this party together

25:49.955 --> 25:52.923
and trust that

25:52.958 --> 25:55.993
we can be forgiven for making mistakes?

25:58.897 --> 26:00.798
Okay.

