26:40.071 --> 26:43.574
<i>♪ I'm coming home to you. ♪</i>

26:45.744 --> 26:47.745
(Seagulls cawing)

26:50.915 --> 26:52.650
When?

26:52.684 --> 26:55.452
Well, as soon as...

26:55.487 --> 26:57.855
We just wanted to have

26:57.889 --> 27:00.391
a nice Father's Day and...

27:00.425 --> 27:01.792
We were gonna tell you tomorrow.

27:01.826 --> 27:04.461
And where will I live?

27:04.496 --> 27:06.463
At home, with me.

27:06.498 --> 27:09.433
We have no intention
of sending you anywhere.

27:09.467 --> 27:11.535
And I'm so sorry, sweetie,

27:11.569 --> 27:13.537
you thought that's what was going on.

27:13.571 --> 27:15.506
And this is...

27:15.540 --> 27:17.308
it's just a separation, okay?

27:17.342 --> 27:19.343
We're not talking about a divorce here.

27:19.377 --> 27:22.212
Your father rented a house at the beach.

27:22.247 --> 27:24.415
You can see him anytime you want.

27:24.449 --> 27:26.350
Why can't I live with him?

27:26.384 --> 27:30.387
Sophia, your mother is
not responsible for this.

27:30.422 --> 27:33.490
We just need some time apart.

27:33.525 --> 27:35.326
Why?

27:35.360 --> 27:37.294
I mean, if you're not getting divorced,

27:37.329 --> 27:39.430
then why do you need time apart?

27:43.368 --> 27:46.337
Look, sometimes

27:46.371 --> 27:49.139
when you're not with someone,

27:49.174 --> 27:51.275
it helps you remember all
the reasons you want to be.

27:53.211 --> 27:56.180
They're still your mom and dad,

27:56.214 --> 27:58.315
and they still love you,

27:58.350 --> 28:01.318
and I love you.

28:01.353 --> 28:03.287
It's gonna be okay.

28:08.960 --> 28:12.162
I baked some cookies,
if anyone has room left.

28:12.197 --> 28:13.897
Not me. I ate like a horse.

28:13.932 --> 28:15.766
Yeah, everything was fantastic.

28:15.800 --> 28:17.868
- Mike: Thank you.
- It was really delicious. Thank you.

28:17.902 --> 28:21.071
How about a toast? To
our amazing hostesses.

28:21.106 --> 28:23.974
- Cheers.
- A toast to the amazing men in our lives.

28:25.443 --> 28:26.877
<i>Salud.</i>

28:26.911 --> 28:28.946
Brandon, would you like to be excused?

28:28.980 --> 28:31.882
- You look like you could use a nap.
- No, I'm good.

28:31.916 --> 28:34.084
Yeah, you look real tired.
Come on, I'll tuck you in.

28:34.152 --> 28:36.019
Stef: Aww, Daddy.

28:36.054 --> 28:38.655
All right.

28:38.690 --> 28:40.958
Please, don't get up. I'm
just gonna clear the dishes.

28:40.992 --> 28:43.060
Let me help you with that.

28:45.864 --> 28:47.698
Stef: Thanks, love.

28:47.732 --> 28:49.867
- Thank you.
- Thanks, Donald.

28:49.901 --> 28:53.504
So, Donald, are you
still in the same place?

28:53.538 --> 28:54.905
Oh, no, actually I had to move.

28:54.939 --> 28:57.574
I should probably give you my new address.

28:57.609 --> 28:59.810
Yeah, that'd be nice.
Nice to know where you are.

28:59.844 --> 29:01.712
Do you think Callie is gonna be home soon?

29:01.746 --> 29:03.647
I'd kind of love to see her.

29:03.681 --> 29:05.582
I'm sure she'd love to see you too,

29:05.617 --> 29:08.385
but she's probably gonna be late.

29:12.757 --> 29:14.625
Thanks, Adam.

29:14.659 --> 29:16.660
No problem. You're welcome.

29:16.694 --> 29:19.696
Listen, I've been doing some reading

29:19.731 --> 29:22.499
about, you know,

29:22.534 --> 29:25.636
kids Connor's age coming out.

29:25.670 --> 29:29.406
And, well,

29:29.441 --> 29:31.408
some L.G.B.T. experts say

29:31.443 --> 29:34.478
that it's better for kids to
wait till they get a little older

29:34.512 --> 29:36.480
to go public, you know,

29:36.514 --> 29:39.283
so they can better cope
with bullying and stuff

29:39.317 --> 29:42.286
in school and sports teams and all that.

29:42.320 --> 29:46.323
Well, that ship has sailed,
at least at Anchor Beach.

29:46.357 --> 29:48.325
But I can promise you

29:48.359 --> 29:51.328
we have a very strict no-bullying policy.

29:51.362 --> 29:53.564
What do you mean, that ship has sailed?

29:57.235 --> 29:58.435
Hey.

29:58.470 --> 30:01.338
So the whole school knows you're gay?

30:09.506 --> 30:11.101
Was it you? Are you the
one who told everybody?

30:11.102 --> 30:11.830
- No.
- No, we...

30:11.832 --> 30:13.377
- I got outed.
- By whom?

30:13.378 --> 30:14.099
I don't know.

30:14.124 --> 30:15.425
I'm sorry. I thought your father knew.

30:15.459 --> 30:17.093
What does that matter, Adam?

30:17.127 --> 30:19.429
'Cause I happen to care
what people think, okay?

30:19.463 --> 30:22.298
About you or your son?

30:22.522 --> 30:25.591
Well, it seems like it's
his business who knows.

30:25.626 --> 30:28.260
What, you want your
son getting bullied too?

30:28.295 --> 30:29.428
No.

30:29.593 --> 30:32.328
I want my son to be proud of who he is.

30:32.362 --> 30:34.663
Getting bullied at home
is worse than anything

30:34.698 --> 30:37.299
he's gonna face out in the world.

30:43.272 --> 30:45.206
That's not my intention.

30:47.176 --> 30:49.244
I know, Dad.

30:58.388 --> 31:00.356
Feeling better?

31:00.390 --> 31:01.757
Yeah, a little.

31:01.791 --> 31:03.592
Have a few drinks last night?

31:05.628 --> 31:07.563
- No.
- No?

31:07.597 --> 31:09.665
I think I know a hangover
when I see one, Brandon.

31:09.699 --> 31:11.567
Dad, I...

31:11.601 --> 31:13.736
Look, I get it. There's peer pressure,

31:13.770 --> 31:16.405
kids like to have parties.

31:16.439 --> 31:19.541
Brandon, there's a reason it's
illegal to drink before you're 21.

31:19.576 --> 31:21.477
Teenagers make bad decisions.

31:21.511 --> 31:23.445
They're not mature enough
to drink responsibly.

31:23.480 --> 31:25.414
I didn't even want to drink.

31:25.448 --> 31:27.549
I just...

31:27.584 --> 31:29.451
believe me, I regretted it.

31:29.486 --> 31:31.720
Well, at least you made one good decision.

31:31.755 --> 31:34.723
You didn't try to drive home last night.

31:34.758 --> 31:37.659
Look, how is Idyllwild otherwise?

31:37.694 --> 31:41.463
Uh...

31:41.498 --> 31:42.698
It's intense.

31:42.732 --> 31:44.299
I don't know.

31:44.334 --> 31:46.535
The people are so competitive.

31:46.569 --> 31:48.604
I thought I made a friend,

31:48.638 --> 31:52.408
but he ended up stabbing me in the back.

31:52.442 --> 31:55.444
You gotta rise above all that, you
know. Do your work, stay focused,

31:55.478 --> 31:57.546
don't get involved in the petty stuff.

31:57.580 --> 31:59.982
Yeah.

32:00.497 --> 32:02.598
Hey, can I ask you something?

32:02.632 --> 32:05.501
Mm.

32:05.535 --> 32:10.205
How would you feel
about me fostering a kid?

32:15.178 --> 32:16.211
B?

32:37.300 --> 32:39.501
- Hey, Dad.
- Yeah?

32:39.536 --> 32:42.171
I love you.

32:46.409 --> 32:48.210
Love you.

32:51.147 --> 32:52.447
Thanks for coming.

32:52.482 --> 32:54.449
Thanks for the invitation.

32:54.484 --> 32:57.386
It meant a lot, Jude.

32:57.420 --> 33:00.255
You know,

33:00.290 --> 33:02.257
it's not good for any of us

33:02.292 --> 33:04.326
to keep secrets about who we are.

33:04.360 --> 33:07.362
And you have everything to be proud of,

33:07.397 --> 33:09.264
except me.

33:09.299 --> 33:11.934
If you don't want to tell
people where I've been

33:11.968 --> 33:14.269
and what I've done, that's okay.

33:14.304 --> 33:16.271
You don't have to.

33:16.306 --> 33:18.073
But you don't have to protect me either.

33:18.107 --> 33:21.109
You know, my story...
it's part of your story.

33:21.144 --> 33:23.278
You want to tell it... you got every right.

33:23.313 --> 33:26.215
I just...

33:26.249 --> 33:29.318
Just want to let you
know I'm okay with that.

33:37.160 --> 33:39.061
Can we stay in touch?

33:39.095 --> 33:41.129
Yeah, you bet.

33:44.867 --> 33:47.936
Hey, there's Callie.

33:47.971 --> 33:49.938
Hey.

33:49.973 --> 33:52.174
Donald, this is Robert.

34:04.053 --> 34:05.921
It's nice to meet you, Donald.

34:07.824 --> 34:09.925
You too.

34:13.862 --> 34:15.931
I have to get a bus.

34:15.965 --> 34:18.065
Don't want to miss it.

34:26.141 --> 34:28.844
In case you forgot,

34:28.878 --> 34:33.081
Donald was there for you when he wasn't.

34:33.116 --> 34:35.984
And he's just as much
your dad as he is mine.

34:50.915 --> 34:53.784
- Thanks for today.
- Yeah, hold on.

34:55.587 --> 34:57.521
Sit down. I want to talk to you.

35:03.494 --> 35:06.396
Um...

35:06.431 --> 35:10.201
Okay, look, I understand
that you're angry with Donald.

35:10.235 --> 35:13.103
But Jude's right. He
was there when I wasn't.

35:13.138 --> 35:16.307
Because he pretended he was my
father, and he never told you about me.

35:16.341 --> 35:18.275
I'm sure he was just
respecting your mother's wishes,

35:18.310 --> 35:20.377
and he didn't just pretend to
be your father, he raised you.

35:20.412 --> 35:23.180
He killed my mother. It's
his fault that she's dead.

35:23.215 --> 35:25.115
He made a mistake.

35:26.985 --> 35:30.054
All right, it was a
terrible, horrible mistake.

35:30.088 --> 35:32.056
He never should have
gotten behind the wheel,

35:32.090 --> 35:34.325
but your mother never should have
gotten in that car with him either.

35:34.359 --> 35:36.327
- So now it's her fault?
- No, it's not.

35:36.361 --> 35:38.963
But we've all made mistakes.

35:38.997 --> 35:41.999
The only difference is how
much suffering they cause.

35:42.033 --> 35:43.868
Donald... he might be out of prison,

35:43.902 --> 35:45.970
but he will never be free of that guilt

35:46.004 --> 35:48.138
and that remorse.

35:48.173 --> 35:50.241
Can you imagine that?

35:50.275 --> 35:52.243
He still could have fought for us.

35:55.280 --> 35:57.214
Look, I had...

36:01.186 --> 36:03.053
I was unfaithful to Jill.

36:03.088 --> 36:06.023
That's why we're separating.

36:06.057 --> 36:08.859
I was selfish,

36:08.894 --> 36:11.996
I broke my promise, and
I hurt her very much.

36:17.068 --> 36:21.105
I think I've been telling
myself all this time

36:21.139 --> 36:23.741
that it was your mother

36:23.775 --> 36:25.876
that was the love of my life.

36:25.911 --> 36:27.912
And I think sometimes I treated Jill

36:27.946 --> 36:30.681
like something I settled for.

36:33.818 --> 36:35.786
But the way she stood by me

36:35.820 --> 36:37.788
when you came into our lives,

36:37.822 --> 36:39.957
with her love and
support, it made me realize

36:39.991 --> 36:42.626
that she is...

36:42.661 --> 36:45.696
everything.

36:46.998 --> 36:51.568
She's the love of my life,

36:51.603 --> 36:53.837
along with Sophia, and now you.

36:56.641 --> 36:59.610
And I was very foolish not to see that.

37:03.581 --> 37:05.950
My point is,

37:05.984 --> 37:09.820
I am not a better man than Donald.

37:09.854 --> 37:12.456
I'm just luckier.

37:17.595 --> 37:19.697
So, you a cop too?

37:19.731 --> 37:21.432
Actually, I am.

37:21.466 --> 37:23.867
Callie's foster mom and I are partners,

37:23.902 --> 37:26.670
and... we used to be married.

37:26.705 --> 37:29.440
Sounds complicated.

37:29.474 --> 37:31.542
No, it's good, you know?

37:31.576 --> 37:34.411
Stef and her wife are
gonna adopt Callie, so...

37:34.446 --> 37:35.679
What?

37:35.714 --> 37:38.449
Like, Callie has two moms?

37:38.483 --> 37:39.717
Yep.

37:39.751 --> 37:41.719
Like you said, it's complicated.

37:41.753 --> 37:45.456
I don't know. Having two
moms sounds kind of cool.

37:45.490 --> 37:46.690
So where's yours?

37:46.725 --> 37:48.692
She's in a institution.

37:48.727 --> 37:50.728
She's mentally ill.

37:50.762 --> 37:53.564
And your dad?

37:53.598 --> 37:55.566
He's dead.

37:57.469 --> 37:58.802
I got a grandma.

37:58.837 --> 38:00.471
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

38:00.505 --> 38:02.473
She raised me and my brother, after.

38:02.507 --> 38:04.541
- Is she...
- She's alive.

38:04.576 --> 38:06.643
She's in a home. She's got dementia.

38:06.678 --> 38:09.680
She couldn't take care of us anymore,
so they put us in Foster care.

38:11.516 --> 38:13.684
Well, look, I ran your brother's
name through the system,

38:13.718 --> 38:15.786
and he hasn't been arrested.

38:19.457 --> 38:24.561
- That's good, right?
- If he's not in jail...

38:26.398 --> 38:28.365
Can you see if he's dead?

38:30.835 --> 38:32.803
'Cause he's all I got.

38:32.837 --> 38:35.406
<i>♪ There are times ♪</i>

38:35.440 --> 38:38.776
<i>♪ that I would hide alone ♪</i>

38:38.810 --> 38:41.445
<i>♪ but I'll find my way ♪</i>

38:41.479 --> 38:44.381
<i>♪ back home ♪</i>

38:45.617 --> 38:49.319
<i>♪ and I'll find my way back... ♪</i>

38:49.354 --> 38:51.488
Dad!

38:51.523 --> 38:54.525
<i>♪ I want to give my lies ♪</i>

38:54.559 --> 38:58.796
<i>♪ to someone else... ♪</i>

38:58.830 --> 39:02.399
I just wanted to say

39:02.434 --> 39:04.701
happy Father's Day.

39:04.736 --> 39:07.337
<i>♪ But I'll find my way ♪</i>

39:07.372 --> 39:09.573
<i>♪ back home ♪</i>

39:10.775 --> 39:12.776
<i>♪ and I'll find my way back... ♪</i>

39:12.811 --> 39:15.412
I made you miss your bus.

39:16.748 --> 39:18.782
It's okay. There'll be another one.

39:19.818 --> 39:23.487
<i>♪ And there's no song ♪</i>

39:23.521 --> 39:27.424
<i>♪ I'd rather sing ♪</i>

39:27.459 --> 39:30.761
<i>♪ I'll find my way back home. ♪</i>

39:30.795 --> 39:32.763
So we have three birth uncles

39:32.797 --> 39:34.498
and eight birth cousins.

39:34.532 --> 39:35.766
- Wow.
- And everyone was super nice.

39:35.800 --> 39:38.635
They're all really close,
and super sweet to Ana too.

39:38.670 --> 39:41.371
Well, it sounds like everyone
had a really good Father's Day.

39:41.406 --> 39:43.540
And speaking of...

39:43.575 --> 39:44.741
Right.

39:48.746 --> 39:51.548
- Lena: Oh my gosh.
- Stef: Oh, what?

39:53.418 --> 39:55.452
Well, even though it's Father's Day...

39:55.487 --> 39:56.620
We wanted you to know...

39:56.654 --> 39:58.689
That we are grateful for all our mothers

39:58.723 --> 40:00.858
and fathers, but mostly...

40:00.892 --> 40:03.494
We're grateful for our parents.

40:03.561 --> 40:05.562
- Oh my gosh.
- Sounds like a card.

40:05.597 --> 40:07.564
(All giggle)

40:07.599 --> 40:09.800
That's very sweet. Did you rehearse that?

40:09.834 --> 40:12.436
- Mariana made us.
- And they loved it.

40:12.470 --> 40:13.637
They're from Jesus too.

40:13.671 --> 40:14.671
(Phone rings)

40:14.706 --> 40:17.441
- Oh, guys.
- I got it.

40:17.475 --> 40:19.443
Hello. Hey.

40:19.477 --> 40:21.578
What's up?

40:21.613 --> 40:23.780
You did? Okay.

40:23.815 --> 40:26.617
I don't know. A couple of weeks.

40:28.753 --> 40:31.421
I will ask her.

40:31.456 --> 40:33.423
Ask me what?

40:42.534 --> 40:43.834
Hey, Callie.

40:43.868 --> 40:46.637
Would you mind coming in
here for a second, please?

40:53.578 --> 40:55.646
Have a seat.

40:58.716 --> 41:00.450
What's going on?

41:00.485 --> 41:01.685
Well...

41:01.719 --> 41:05.389
Um, I went to juvie to talk with A.J.,

41:05.423 --> 41:08.425
and I've...

41:08.459 --> 41:10.627
we've decided I'm gonna foster him.

41:10.662 --> 41:12.579
Stef: Yeah, it's gonna take some time

41:12.580 --> 41:14.475
for Mike to get his license, so

41:14.576 --> 41:17.810
in the meantime, A.J.'s
gonna stay here with us.

41:17.911 --> 41:18.711
Okay?

